		<table width="100%">
		<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    General ideas for a Shaman in Everfrost part 2.</b></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><A href="mailto:Ranger_Won@bwn.net">Jaroth</a> | 
		            12/2/1999 5:35:56 PM</b></font></p>
		         <a href="guides.asp">
		         <font face="verdana" size="2">Return to guide listing.</font></a>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">Last time I focussed on fighting and battles. Now I am going to cencentrate on spells and money. Since it seems you need money for everything in EQ you'll want to make as much as possible. It can be quite difficult since Everfrost itself doesnt generate too much income other than a few silver here and there. So as a lwoer lvl you start with a couple spells, use these as much as possible while fighting, always keep yourself buffed. Too get some good money for the time being kill skeltons, Decaying is best not the vengfuls. Also gnolls give you some money. Your probably wondering why I am going on and on about money, well thats because you need money to buy spells. Right now your most important spells until lvl 5 will be Burst of flame, frost rift, minor heal, dextrous aura, gate, feet like cat, and conjure water. If you conjure water all the time you same the money from buying the water which goes for around 1sp and a couple copper. It also gets your conjure up which is good since a spell in the future really helps more if you have your conjure up. Gate allows you to teleport home from anywhere, depending on where your bound, at this point you should be bound to the entrance to halas. Frost rift is better than busrt of flame but BOF works well when your low on mana and cant cast FR. I still do this as a lvl 13 shaman, it adds that little bit of help. All the other spells mentioned are buffs which are very helpful, since as a shaman you cant stand there and take a beating like a warrior can.<BR>
When your out on the planes it is good to either find a hunting party of partner and share the money coming in, loot in alphabetical order. At this point you still wont make more than a few gold for something, which is the case for me still. ) When you hit lvl 9, if you don't get sick of the game and quit, all your efforts pay off because now you start getting the real spells. Spirit of the Wolf, Tainted breath, Spirit of the bear, endure disease. I am just naming spells that have helped me a lot, there are many more spells than this, and you can go back and get them if you really want to, but chances are when your a higher lvl there is a better version of the spell.<BR>
Spirit of the wold, aka SOW is the absolute best spell in the world. It speeds your runing up and allows you to run from battles when you know your gunna die, as long as your hit points aren't too low. You can run anywhere with this one and not worry about being chased even if you are they cant catch up to you, until your out of this area...I'll let you explore. Tainted breath is great because it given damage over time so you can kill some things that con yellow to you by running around the zone. Not a good idea in everfrost though, especially on the plains, too many tings will come after you. Spirit of the bear adds to your stamina allowing you to run farther and fight longer. Also serpent sight, a difficult spell to get unless you have a friend that isn't a barbarian, you can either get it in the Gypsy camp in the oasis near freeport, not a good idea, or have a friend run to Qeynos and buy it for you, not quite sure where it can be found, all I know is thet some merchants there don't like barbarians. Endure disease adds to your disease points which is helpful when fighting spiders in everfrost.<BR>
At this point you get Minor healing, some people say it isn't worth the mana point to hit point ratio but I don't care, because at lvl 8 you should be able to meditate. Around this time you can start hunting in erud's crossing or the karanas. But as with every zone there are things to watch out for. North Ro, I think I have mentioned it before, is a great place to hunt, but a long journey. You may want to join a guild, I get a teleport from a guild member which helps, then I get a bind to wherever I am. It is very helpful. The only downside to being in Ro is I am so far away from home and whenever I gain a lvl I can use my guild points when I want to, also when I get to a lvl here I get new spells I cant buy them, so if someone is giving a free teleport to North Karans take it if you are close to a new lvl where you get new spells, buy them ahead of time, don't worry about a bind in halas again if you want to go back to Ro. You can just run to halas from Karanas and do what you need to do then gate back. See its helpful. Heh heh. I will update as often as I can since I am only lvl 13 I cant give advise on what to do past this point. But a thing to remember, keep your money, spells get expensive. 
			<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
					</p>
